Japanese Kana-to-Kanji conversion engine that used the Hidden Markov Model.
A considerable part of the code originates in the ChaSen. It is possible to use
it on Emacs through Egg. Moreover, it is possible to use it with uim.
It aims to input the long sentence in accuracy.

Besides this, it is extensible with Scheme, written by functional programming
language OCaml and C are features.
